{"lemma":"خَبَّةٍ","slug":"خَبَّةٍ","root":"خ.ب.ب","root_slug":"خ-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9830","n9831","n9832"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to subside, to sink in"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to alight and abode in a depressed tract or ground, in order that one’s place might not be known (like e. g. to avoid claims upon one’s hospitability)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become deceitful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to trot, to gallop easily"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to waw, to undulate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"deception, fraud, verbal noun of خَبَّ (ḵabba) (form I)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"deceiver, cheater","examples":[{"text":"لَا يَدْخُلُ الْجَنَّةَ خِبٌّ وَلَا مَنَّانٌ وَلَا بَخِيلٌ","english":"The cheater, the laudicenus and the miser don’t enter paradise."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"waw, wave"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9830","headword_ar":"خَبَّةٌ","root":"xb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~apN","text_ar":"خِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9831","headword_ar":"خُبَّةٌ","root":"xb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~apN","text_ar":"خِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place where water collects and remains"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stagnates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and around which grow herbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tract of land neither fruitful nor unfruitful, between two other tracts of land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubabN","text_ar":"خُبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHn:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tract of land between that which abounds with herbage and that which is unproductive:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ru-beh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a narrow tract of soft land abounding with herbage, not rugged nor plain, but inclining to be plain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh;) but ADk disapproves of this explanation: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tract producing herbage between two long and elevated tracts of sand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ibn-Nujeym:) and, accord. to AA, also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Also, or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxab~apN","text_ar":"مَخَبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to different copies of the K, or both, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bottom"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTon","text_ar":"بَطْن"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a valley."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["AA","K","TA","AHn"]},{"entry_id":"n9832","headword_ar":"خِبَّةٌ","root":"xb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xub~apN","text_ar":"خُبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~apN","text_ar":"خَبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A narrow tract,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of sand; [in one copy of the A, I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~apN","text_ar":"خِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus explained; but in another, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxab~apN","text_ar":"مَخَبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is written in the place of the former of these two words;] or of clouds; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As:) or, of sand,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what resembles a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAliq","text_ar":"فَالِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed tract between two hills"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except in its being wider and more spreading, and not having abrupt sides;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says AHn in explaining"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xb~p","text_ar":"خبّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus in the TA] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or all three signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of rag like a fillet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xub~N","text_ar":"خُبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lh:) or the last two ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xbybp","text_ar":"خبيبة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xb~","text_ar":"خبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of rag from a garment, with which one binds his arm"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA.) [Hence,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN A^axobaAbN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ اَخْبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, K,) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahobaAbN","text_ar":"اَهْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vwb xibabN","text_ar":"ثوب خِبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, JK, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hibabN","text_ar":"هِبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vwb xabaAy^ibu","text_ar":"ثوب خَبَايِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"habaAy^ibu","text_ar":"هَبَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [the latter word in the first of these phrases being pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xub~N","text_ar":"خُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; that in the second, pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~pN","text_ar":"خِبّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that in the third, pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, rent in pieces, ragged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tattered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, JK, S, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] It is also said that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~ap","text_ar":"خِبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a garment, or piece of cloth, is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tur~ap","text_ar":"طُرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: and accord. to Sh, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xub~ap","text_ar":"خُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof is its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tur~ap","text_ar":"طُرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xb~p","text_ar":"خبّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the TA] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of rag which a woman wears, covering her head with it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"erroneously written by Lth"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hn~p","text_ar":"حنّة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Az, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~apN","text_ar":"خِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its two vars., and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybapN","text_ar":"خَبِيبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaAy^ibu","text_ar":"خَبَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A streak"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the flesh"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearing in the skin, occasioned by the loss of flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["As","TA","S","K","Lh","JK"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}